With the intention of better showing the characteristics of the invention, hereafter, as example without any limitative character, some preferred embodiments are described of a glazing panel and an assembly of glazing panels in accordance with the invention, with reference to the accompanying drawings, wherein:
figures 1 and 2 represent a front view on two different assemblies of glazing panels in accordance with the present invention;
figure 3 represents on a larger scale a cross-sectional view, indicated by III-III in figure 1, through a border of a first embodiment of a glazing panel according to the invention,;
figure 4 represents in a way similar to figure 3 a cross-sectional view through the border of another embodiment of a glazing panel in accordance with the present invention;
figure 5 is a cross-sectional view on a spacer frame structure of still another preferred embodiment of a glazing panel in accordance with the present invention;
figures 6 and 7 represent cross-sectional views similar to figure 3, through a glazing panel wherein the spacer frame structure of figure 5 is applied, in full line when the glazing panel is not subjected to external load, and in dash line after deformation of the glazing panel under a certain load;
figures 8 and 9, are similar views as figures 5 and 6 for still another embodiment of a spacer frame structure and the corresponding glazing panel in accordance with the invention respectively;
figure 10 is another alternative for the spacer frame structure represented in figure 5;
figures 11 and 12 are views similar to figure 6 of a cross-section through still two other embodiments of a glazing panel in accordance with the invention;
figure 13 is a perspective view of the embodiment of a spacer frame structure represented in figure 5, in a disassembled status; and,
figure 14 is a perspective view of a glazing panel according to the invention represented in figures 6 and 7, which is partly assembled and which comprises the spacer frame structure of figure 13.
